  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> A banner?\r\n\r\nI would use banner only for good news, they take too much space for such a \"I have a problem\" matter (kind of feels like everyone has issues with the doc, which is not the case).\r\n\r\nI would put it at the bottom of every webpages. Most probably people will read deeply any webpage to understand that they are missing some information.\r\n\r\nSo I propose to add \"Missing some documentation? [Let us know](LINK TO NEW ISSUE)!\" at the end of every page.",
